Flask Task Manager with Authentication (MySQL)
Overview
The toughest project: a task manager with user accounts, authentication, and a dashboard showing tasks by deadline.

Features
User registration and login.

Password hashing with Werkzeug.

Add tasks with title, description, deadline.

Dashboard with line chart showing tasks by deadline.

Logout functionality.

Project Structure
Code
TaskManager/
├── app.py
└── templates/
    ├── register.html
    ├── login.html
    └── dashboard.html
Database Setup
sql
CREATE DATABASE task_manager;
USE task_manager;

CREATE TABLE users (
    id INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
    username VARCHAR(255) UNIQUE NOT NULL,
    password_hash VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    role ENUM('admin','user') DEFAULT 'user'
);

CREATE TABLE tasks (
    id INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id INT,
    title VARCHAR(255),
    description TEXT,
    deadline DATE,
    completed BOOLEAN DEFAULT FALSE,
    FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES users(id)
);
Workflow
User registers and logs in.

Tasks are added and linked to the user.

Dashboard queries tasks grouped by deadline.

Chart.js renders line chart of tasks count vs. deadline.

Limitations
No background reminders yet.

No real‑time updates.

Only basic role handling.

Future Enhancements
Add Celery + Redis for reminders.

Add Flask‑SocketIO for real‑time updates.

Add Flask‑Mail for email notifications.

Add role‑based dashboards.
